value.name: Louis Leroy - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Louis Leroy (1812 - 1885) was a French 19th-century printmaker, painter, and playwright. Biography. He is remembered as the journalist and art critic for the French satirical newspaper Le Charivari, who coined the term "impressionists" to satirise the artists now known by the word.
